visual_elements.description: A key defining line types: solid line for Curb, dashed line for Lot line, hatched rectangle for Sidewalk, thin solid line for Required setbacks, and light gray shaded area for Buildable area.

Diagram A: 'Flag lot'. Shows a rectangular lot with a narrow access strip to the street. It has a 'Front yard', 'Rear yard', and 'Interior-side yard' on both sides. An annotation indicates 'Front lot line is closest and most parallel to street.' Another annotation points to a 'Front setback' of 10' instead of 20'.

Diagram B: 'Corner lot'. Shows a rectangular lot at a street corner. It has a 'Front yard', 'Rear yard', and 'Interior-side yard' on two sides, and a 'Street-side yard' on one side. A dimension of 16' is shown for the 'Street-side yard'.

Diagram C: 'Substandard Corner lot w/frontage < 50''. Shows a rectangular lot at a street corner, similar to B but with a smaller frontage. It has a 'Front yard', 'Rear yard', 'Interior-side yard', and 'Street-side yard'. An annotation indicates 'Street side setback is 10' instead of 16''. Another annotation points to 'Front lot line is shortest of the two frontages.' A dimension of 10' is shown for the 'Street-side yard'.
Diagram D: 'Through lot'. Shows a rectangular lot with frontages on two parallel streets. It has a 'Front yard', 'Rear yard', and 'Interior-side yard' on both sides.

Diagram E: 'Wedge shaped lot'. Shows a pie-shaped lot with a curved frontage on a street. It has a 'Front yard' and 'Interior-side yard' on both radial sides. An annotation states: 'Wedge shaped lots don't have rear lot lines. The rear yard is determined by a 20' radius from intersection of side lot lines.'
Diagram F: 'Lot with more than 4 sides'. Shows an irregular polygon-shaped lot with a straight frontage on a street. It has a 'Front yard', 'Rear yard', and 'Interior-side yard' on multiple sides.

Diagram G: 'Lot with more than 4 sides'. Shows an L-shaped lot with a straight frontage on a street. It has a 'Front yard', 'Rear yard', and 'Interior-side yard' on multiple sides. An annotation indicates 'Rear lot line is farthest and most parallel to street.'
